For this purpose, the strengths of the teams are estimated by the Football Club Elo Ratings, available at http://clubelo.com/ .4The Elo rating is based on past results such that the same outcome against a stronger opponent has more value and the influence of a game decreases after new games are played (Van Eetvelde and Ley, 2019).
While there 4There is a parallel project at http://elofootball.com/ , which also measures the strength of European clubs by the Elo method.
The Elo ratings of http://clubelo.com/ modify the standard Elo system by taking home advantage and goal difference into account.
The underlying database contains all international matches played in the UEFA Champions League, Europa League, and Conference League, as well as in their predecessors (see http://clubelo.com/Data ).

According to the methodology of the Club Elo rating (see http://clubelo.com/ System ), the a priori probability that team 𝑖with an Elo of 𝐸𝑖advances against team 𝑗 with an Elo of 𝐸𝑗is given by 𝑊𝑒=1 1 + 10−𝑑/𝑠(1) in the one-legged matches of the preliminary round PR, and by 𝑊* 𝑒=1 1 + 10−√ 2𝑑/𝑠(2) in the two-legged home-and-away clashes of qualifying rounds Q1–Q3 and PO, where 𝑑=𝐸𝑖−𝐸𝑗is the difference between the Elo ratings of the two teams, and 𝑠is a scaling parameter.
